<h2 id="alert--prompt">Alert &amp; prompt</h2>

<p><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">alert()</code> mostra una finestra di avviso contenente il testo specificato mentre <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">prompt()</code> mostra una finestra di dialogo che chiede allâ€™utente di inserire del testo.</p>

<div class="language-html highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="cp">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</span>
<span class="nt">&lt;html</span> <span class="na">lang=</span><span class="s">"en"</span><span class="nt">&gt;</span>
<span class="nt">&lt;head&gt;</span>
    <span class="nt">&lt;meta</span> <span class="na">charset=</span><span class="s">"UTF-8"</span><span class="nt">&gt;</span>
    <span class="nt">&lt;meta</span> <span class="na">name=</span><span class="s">"viewport"</span> <span class="na">content=</span><span class="s">"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"</span><span class="nt">&gt;</span>
    <span class="nt">&lt;title&gt;</span>Document<span class="nt">&lt;/title&gt;</span>
<span class="nt">&lt;/head&gt;</span>
<span class="nt">&lt;body&gt;</span>
    <span class="nt">&lt;script&gt;</span>
        <span class="c1">//Salva l'input ricevuto in una variabile cioÃ¨ un contenitore testuale </span>
        <span class="nx">myName</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nx">prompt</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="dl">'</span><span class="s1">Come ti chiami?</span><span class="dl">'</span><span class="p">);</span>
        <span class="nx">alert</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="dl">"</span><span class="s2">Il tuo nome Ã¨ ..</span><span class="dl">"</span><span class="p">);</span>
        <span class="c1">//Stampa il valore testuale contenuto nella variabile</span>
        <span class="nx">alert</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nx">myName</span><span class="p">);</span>
    <span class="nt">&lt;/script&gt;</span>
<span class="nt">&lt;/body&gt;</span>
<span class="nt">&lt;/html&gt;</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<p><img src="./images/alert-prompt.gif" alt="" /></p>

<p>Approfondimenti sul metodo <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">alert()</code> dellâ€™oggetto <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">Window</code> li trovate su <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/it/docs/Web/API/Window/alert">MDN - Window.alert()</a> mentre approfondimenti sul metodo <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">prompt()</code> dellâ€™oggetto <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">Window</code> li trovate su <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/it/docs/Web/API/Window/prompt">MDN - Window.prompt()</a></p>

<h2 id="commenti">Commenti</h2>

<p>I commenti sono linee testuali non processate dallâ€™interprete utili per la documentazione del codice. In javascritp ci sono due tipi di sintassi permesse per lâ€™inserimento dei commenti.</p>
<ul>
  <li><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">// comment</code>: per commenti inline</li>
  <li><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">/* comment */</code>: per commenti su linee multiple</li>
</ul>

<div class="language-js highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="c1">//inline comment</span>

<span class="cm">/*
multi line comment
console.log('ciao a tutti');
*/</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

